data.text: Guyana was originally three Dutch Latin American colonies. After the colony was ceded to the British in 1814, the three were combined into British Guiana. After independence in 1966, it established a socialist governance that for a long time was greatly influence by the CIA and other outside players Guyana has undergone several peaceful changes of power through free and fair elections and is home to the headquarters of the Caribbean Community, an organization of Caribbean and Latin American nations.
